				\begin{document}$${\Phi }_{{{\text{UC}}}}$$\end{document}, is 0.5 or 50%. The upconversion quantum yield depends on the excitation intensity—it first increases with higher excitation intensity until it reaches a plateau of constant quantum yield. Therefore, it is relevant to define a threshold intensity, Ith\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
